// Spec 2 · Plan 6 — port of aeon/games/sonic4/data/sound/song_drumtest.asm.
//
// A faithful, byte-exact port of a real Aeon packed-music data blob (Music
// format v0). The AS original is a pure `dc.b` stream between a start label
// (`Song_DrumTest`) and an end label, followed by `align 2` (a no-op here — the
// stream is 82 bytes, already even). In .emp it is one fixed-size byte array;
// the modern front-end emits exactly these bytes (no implicit padding).
//
// @as_compat marks this as a faithful port opted into the byte-diff contract
// (Plan 6, D-P6.3): it silences the modernization / faithful-port lints for the
// module. On this data-only path its byte effect is nil (proven byte-neutral by
// the harness) — its load-bearing width/lint pinning rides instruction ports.
module data.sound.song_drumtest in song_drumtest
@as_compat

